definition: Compound structure, name, and other properties have been evaluated through a documented process for a database or library.
Structure has been measured and derived empirically through a peer-reviewed process.
Structure that is a homolog (differing in CF2 chain lengths) of an empirically-derived structure, but has not been observed empirically.
Structure has been predicted through documented in silico processes, but has not been observed empirically.
Structure has been reported in documentation (e.g., patent, safety data sheet), but has not been observed empirically.
Limited information to support structure, only a formula exists
